CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1962, pg. A16 reads: "A Noble Salute - Mecca Temple 2, AANOMS, recently sponsored a testimonial banquet in honor of Past Grand Potentate Earl D. Johnson and Potentate Jess Johnston. Shown at the affair at York Masonic Hall are (seated, left to right): Emmett Woods, guest speaker; Mrs. Henderson, Mrs. Mittie Tillery of the Aged Ministers' and Laymen's Home, and Rev. Eugene Goodman.  Shown standing are: Nobles W. Carter, J. Davis, Johnson Morant, C. Davis, M. Bradford, G. Corbett.  Second row: U. Middleton, W. Hutchinson, J. Johnston, the honoree; M. Newell, K. Royster, L. Truly, E. Picker, J. Durden.  Third row: J.R. West, E. Cole, E.D. Johnson, honoree; S.J. Carter, W. Neverson.  Back row: E. Rayford, L. Davis and Mr. Webb. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mecca Temple Shriners, from left, seated: Emmett Woods, Mrs. Henderson, Mittie Tillery, and Rev. Eugene Goodman; standing: W. Carter, J. Davis, Johnson Morant, C. Davis, M. Bradford, G. Corbett; second row: U. Middleton, W. Hutchinson, Jesse Johnston, M. Newell, K. Royster, L. Truly, E. Picker, J. Durden; third row: J.R. West, E. Cole, Earl D. Johnson, S.J. Carter, W. Neverson; back row: E. Rayford, L. Davis, and Mr. Webb, gathered for testimonial banquet in York Masonic Hall, another version
